Poor lecturer. I stopped going in October. Do assigned questions and refer to the solutions manual and you will be fine. Term tests were very easy, however the final exam was quite difficult so be sure to prepare heavily for that. Abe is good at organizing the course in terms of dates and information, however has relatively useless lectures.

He was the course coordinator for when I had him so that was a plus. At first his teaching style may be daunting for a first student who is used to having their hand held in high school but you get used to it. Accepts question during lecture. DO NOT CORRECT HIM unless for numerical error. I would consider the textbook optional; just do old tests

He'll spend lots of time with students, if any questions arise. Lectures are clear. The only possible negative is the mass number of hours you'll spend on homework, but that should be expected at UOFT. Overall, he's a superb prof.

Lectures were not helpful at all, always too advanced. Does not teach. He assumes you know the basics and just does the hardest examples. Learned on my own using textbook. Very few people attended lecture. Goes off on things unrelated to course.
